    "title": "Career Opportunity Medical Officer at Columbia Asia",
    "description": "We at Columbia Asia are looking for an experienced Medical Officer based out of Noida. If you are a result-oriented professional with a passion for excellence, we want to hear from you.\n\nAbout Columbia Asia:\nColumbia Asia is a leading organization in the Hybrid sector, committed to excellence, innovation, and employee growth. We offer a dynamic work environment where talent is recognized and rewarded.\n\nKey Responsibilities:\n• Administer medications and treatments as prescribed\n• Diagnose and treat medical conditions following established protocols\n• Attend continuing medical education programs and training\n• Adhere to NABH/JCI accreditation standards\n• Coordinate with multidisciplinary teams for comprehensive patient management\n• Participate in quality improvement initiatives and clinical audits\n• Provide high-quality patient care and maintain patient records\n\nRequired Skills & Qualifications:\n• B.Ed / M.Ed from a recognized institution\n• 10-15 years of relevant experience\n• Proficiency in Patient Care\n• Proficiency in EMR/EHR\n• Proficiency in Diagnostic Skills\n• Proficiency in Pharmacovigilance\n• Proficiency in Medical Coding\n• Proficiency in Clinical Documentation\n• Proficiency in ICD-10\n• Proficiency in CPT Codes\n\nWork Mode: Hybrid - Flexible work-from-home and office\n\nWhat We Offer:\n• International travel opportunities for senior roles\n• Work-from-home flexibility\n• Professional development and training programs\n• Maternity and paternity leave\n• Recognition and rewards programs\n• Provident Fund and Gratuity as per company policy\n• Salary Range: 20 LPA - 40 LPA per annum\n\nLocation: Noida, Uttar Pradesh, India\n\nIf you are excited about this opportunity, apply now and take the next step in your career journey with Columbia Asia!",
